This paper deals with the problem of text-image matching, which is a task that involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new loss function for training the model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of embeddings, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper analyzes the pros and cons of different optimization objectives, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
